[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 1/100 path 2/8 answer="Let \\( V \\) represent the total number of vacuum cleaners Melanie started with.\n\nFirst, let's denote the number of vacuum cleaners she sold at the green house:\n\\[ \\text{Vacuums sold at green house} = \\frac{V}{3} \\]\n\nNext, we know she sold 2 more at the red house:\n\\[ \\text{Vacuums sold at red house} = 2 \\]\n\nThen, calculate the remaining vacuum cleaners after selling to the green and red houses:\n\\[ V - \\left( \\frac{V}{3} + 2 \\right) = V - \\frac{V}{3} - 2 = \\frac{2V}{3} - 2 \\]\n\nMelanie then sold half of what was left at the orange house:\n\\[ \\text{Vacuums sold at orange house} = \\frac{1}{2} \\left( \\frac{2V}{3} - 2 \\right) \\]\n\\[ \\text{Vacuums sold at orange house} = \\frac{V}{3} - 1 \\]\n\nAfter selling to the orange house, we have:\n\\[ \\left( \\frac{2V}{3} - 2 \\right) - \\left( \\frac{V}{3} - 1 \\right) = \\frac{2V}{3} - 2 - \\frac{V}{3} + 1 = \\frac{V}{3} - 1 \\]\n\nAccording to the problem, Melanie has 5 vacuum cleaners left:\n\\[ \\frac{V}{3} - 1 = 5 \\]\n\nSolving for \\( V \\):\n\\[ \\frac{V}{3} = 5 + 1 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{V}{3} = 6 \\]\n\\[ V = 6 \\times 3 \\]\n\\["
